article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 62, Northwestern St. 52
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Stephen F. Austin had four players score in double figures and wrapped up the No. 2 seed in the upcoming Southland Conference tournament with a 62-52 victory over Northwestern State on Saturday night. Antonio Bostic led the way for Stephen F. Austin (19-11, 12-4 Southland) with 18 points. Desmond Haymon scored 14 and Taylor Smith and Jereal Scott had 12 each. Smith had 12 rebounds and Jonathan King had seven to pace Stephen F. Austin, which had a 44-31 advantage on the glass. Stephen F. Austin scored 18 points off turnovers. William Mosley had 17 points to lead Northwestern State (16-15, 8-8), which had a 20-6 scoring advantage off the bench.
